    <h3>9.3 Branch naming &amp; DoR</h3>
    <div class="formula" style="white-space:pre">feature/S-200-omop-parser
defect/D-215-upload-validation
feature/F-102-anon-engine</div>
    <p>CI check blocks PRs without reference to an issue (<code>S-XXX</code>, <code>F-XXX</code>, <code>E-XXX</code>). DoR: Issue Type, Parent, Job Size, BV+TC+RR&amp;OE, Owner.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- 10. Reports and audit -->
  <section id="reports">
    <h2>10. Reports and audit</h2>

    <h3>10.1 Pipeline</h3>
    <div class="formula" style="white-space:pre">/.edpa/snapshots/
  iteration-PI-2026-1.3.json          &larr; frozen snapshot

/.edpa/reports/
  iteration-PI-2026-1.3/
    report-urbanek.md                  &larr; human-readable report
    report-urbanek.json                &larr; machine data
    summary.xlsx                       &larr; summary Excel
    item-costs.xlsx                    &larr; per-item view

/signed/
  PI-2026-1.3-urbanek.pdf             &larr; BankID signed</div>

    <h3>10.2 Freeze rule</h3>
    <p>After Iteration Close: snapshot is <strong>frozen</strong>. Evidence is not overwritten in-place. Every correction is a new revision. Essential for audit defense.</p>

    <h3>10.3 Audit principle</h3>
    <p>Provability rests on 5 pillars:</p>
    <ol class="audit-pillars">
      <li>GitHub delivery evidence</li>
      <li>Capacity registry (YAML)</li>
      <li>Frozen snapshot (reproducible input)</li>
      <li>Reproducible calculation (Score = JS &times; CW; CW = additive aggregation + per-item normalization)</li>
      <li>Signed output (BankID, law 21/2020 Sb.)</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

